 minute for both black-and-white and color prints. This is a fairly slow speed for a laser printer, and we like to see minimum printing speeds of 24 pages per minute on each laser printer.","As we mentioned before, the Brother HL-3040CN offers a basic feature set. There are no wireless printing capabilities available on this device, but it does feature an Ethernet port for networking. There is also an USB 2.0 port available on the device for additional connectivity.","The paper tray on this laser printer will hold up to 250 sheets of paper. This device will also print on a variety of paper types, materials and sizes, including envelopes, labels and paper as large as 8.5 by 14 inches. This laser printer is an ENERGY STAR qualified device, meaning it has met all the specifications proving it offers energy-saving features. It also consumes only 480 watts of power during use. This laser printer is backed by a one-year warranty, but we were disappointed to see that there is only 32MB of installed memory available.","One of the advantages to using the Brother HL-3040CN is the compact size of this laser printer. This device is only 16.1 inches wide, 9.8 inches tall and 18.3 inches deep. It weighs 41.9 pounds, so it is easier to move from one area to another. The control pad for this laser printer is located on the top of the device and features a small display screen and a number of buttons. With such basic features, this device is easy to use and offers a fairly simple interface."]},"id":"091bd50b-5d81-4b4f-a171-ba069ee44ee9","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"7f5eeb57-2043-4df8-8758-da02be3a0cb2","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["If you are looking for a basic printer for your home or small office, the Brother HL-3040CN may be worth your consideration. This laser printer is compact, lightweight and offers 600 x 2400 dpi print resolution. Its monthly duty cycle and printing speeds are not anything spectacular, but this device has enough power to provide overall high performance. This laser printer won’t offer you any advanced options, but if you want something simple, the <strong>Brother HL-3040CN</strong> has what you are looking for."]},"id":"67aca5b6-5ef7-457a-afb0-c4672c274599","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_53190","url":"/brother-hl-3040cn-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"brian-westover","url":"/author/brian-westover","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Brian Westover","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"TBtnELo8v5XHxqU9uBG9c7","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2011-06-29T21:11:43Z","datePublished":"2011-06-29T21:11:43Z","name":"Brother HL-3040CN","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been discontinued.","review":{"verdict":"The Brother HL-3040CN is a basic laser printer that needs several improvements, such as built-in wireless printing and a larger monthly duty cycle before it can be considered a top printing device.","pros":["The Brother HL-3040CN printer offers excellent print resolution at 600 x 2400 dpi."],"cons":["This laser printer offers a measly 25,000 monthly duty cycle and a slow printing speed of 17 pages per minute."]},"strapline":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been discontinued.","language":"en","dateModified":"2011-06-29T21:11:43Z","id":"vuommYJans8bB8B6q5q9cZ","meta":{"title":"Brother HL-3040CN Review - Pros, Cons and Verdict","description":"Visit Top Ten Reviews to read the latest reviews and opinions. Reviews are complete with product ratings and comparisons."},"products":[{"slug":"brother-hl-3040cn","url":"/product/brother-hl-3040cn","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T22:55:29Z","name":"Brother HL-3040CN","dateModified":"2019-04-17T22:55:29Z","id":"gu3W2wYFZzW9o3T3QSWtbL","dateImported":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","site":"toptenreviews"}],"dateImported":"2